es a new data frame df_new by selecting the column with the given name from emoji_table and the TSLA.Adjusted column from final_data, filtering out any rows where the value of the column is 0, and then calculating the mean of the TSLA.Adjusted column. The result is then assigned to an element in the price_by_emoji list with the same name as the column. So, this code calculates the average price for each emoji and stores it in a list called price_by_emoji.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"price_by_emoji = list()\n\ncol_names = colnames(emoji_table)\nfor (col_name in col_names) {\n    df_new <- d %>% select(col1=col_name, price='final_data$TSLA.Adjusted') %>%\n        filter(col1 != 0) %>%\n        summarise(avg_price = mean(price))\n    \n    price_by_emoji[[col_name]] = df_new[1,1]\n}","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-04-14T00:46:20.079445Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-04-14T00:46:20.084007Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-04-14T00:46:20.107791Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":61,"outputs":[{"ename":"ERROR","evalue":"Error in is.data.frame(x): object 'emoji_table' not found\n","traceback":["Error in is.data.frame(x): object 'emoji_table' not found\nTraceback:\n","1. colnames(emoji_table)","2. is.data.frame(x)"],"output_type":"error"}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"df <- data.frame(emoji = names(price_by_emoji), avg_stock_price = unlist(price_by_emoji))\ndf %>% arrange(desc(avg_stock_price)) %>% select(-1)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-04-14T00:46:20.989942Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-04-14T00:46:20.993436Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-04-14T00:46:21.088751Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":62,"outputs":[{"ename":"ERROR","evalue":"\u001b[1m\u001b[33mError\u001b[39m in `arrange()`:\u001b[22m\n\u001b[1m\u001b[22m\u001b[36mℹ\u001b[39m In argument: `..1 = avg_stock_price`.\n\u001b[1mCaused by error:\u001b[22m\n\u001b[33m!\u001b[39m object 'avg_stock_price' not found\n","traceback":["\u001b[1m\u001b[33mError\u001b[39